On 13 April 2012, Lomax played on the 50th Anniversary of the Hamburg-based Star-Club in the Kaiserkeller, with the Star Club All-Star-Band plus Brian Griffiths (Big Three), Bobby Thompson (Dominoes), and Joe Fagin (Strangers), and also with The Undertakers.
On 15 September 2013, Lomax died after a short illness, on the Wirral while staying in England for the wedding of his daughter.
In 2019, one of his songs, New Day from the album Is This What You Want?, was used for a cricket commercial for UK sports channel Sky Sports.
